The Anglican Church of Kenya celebrated its 100 years of existence in the country on Sunday. The anniversary was attended by President Uhuru Kenyatta, First Lady Margaret Kenyatta and Opposition leader Raila Odinga. Graced by Canterbury Archbishop Justin Welby, a message of reconciliation and love took centrestage.  Among other guests present were Church of Kenya Archbishop Jackson ole SapitÂ and Provast Canon Sammy Wainaina.